Sprint 165 V100 validation summary
Date: 2026-05-21
Pod: llm/llamacpp-build-8gpu on gpu-01

Build:
  cd /workspace/ds4
  make -j80 CUDA_ARCH=sm_70 tests/cuda_v100_stage_scheduler_smoke tools/ds4-v100-replay
  PASS

Change under test:
  DS4_V100_TP2_ASYNC_INPUT=1
  Alias: DS4_V100_TP_ROUTED_FFN_ASYNC_INPUT=1

Behavior:
  TP2 async-input mode enqueues peer copies of x, selected, and weights with
  ds4_gpu_tensor_copy_async before launching owner-half compute. Peer-half
  compute runs on the peer default stream after those input copies. Peer output
  copy remains synchronous before owner add to avoid peer scratch reuse hazards.

Stage profile, stage 0, ctx=262144, slots=16:

  Run 1:
    no TP:
      tp2_layers=0 ffn_ms=148.462 total_ms=246.462
    TP2 synchronous input:
      tp2_layers=1 ffn_ms=212.429 total_ms=317.593
    TP2 async input:
      tp2_layers=1 ffn_ms=136.294 total_ms=235.591

  Warm repeat:
    no TP:
      tp2_layers=0 ffn_ms=84.978 total_ms=166.453
    TP2 async input:
      tp2_layers=1 ffn_ms=145.917 total_ms=245.107

Negative gate:
  DS4_V100_TP2_LAYER=2 with only layer-3 TP descriptors and async input:
    cuda_v100_stage_scheduler_smoke: TP2 routed FFN layer 2 has no TP2 bindings
    rc=1
  PASS, failed closed.

Conclusion:
  Async input copies remove a large fraction of the synchronous-overlay penalty
  in the cold A/B/C run, but they do not make the one-layer TP2 overlay
  competitive with the normal production path on a warm repeat. The TP overlay
  should remain diagnostic-only. The next sprint should stop optimizing this
  per-layer overlay and move to either a broader persistent TP/EP scheduler
  boundary or a non-TP larger fused routed-FFN boundary.
